{"insight":"After silence, memory chooses what counts","plainSummary":"After deep silence, what we remember depends on what we have been trained to trust.","atAGlance":"We all meet gaps we cannot describe. When speech returns, memory does not simply report. It gives trust to the self, the blank, the change, the result, or the relation. The real question is which part of the return we are willing to believe.","match":["gap report"],"tags":["memory","silence","trust","practice"]}
